{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645378","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645378"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:17:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:17:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18110"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18110","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18110"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10824"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78288"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10824","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10824"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18110"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63683"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25194"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25197"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26856"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78288","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78288"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe triangular space is one of three anatomical spaces in the shoulder region.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following arteries is found in this space?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Posterior circumflex humeral","Suprascapular","Dorsal scapular","Circumflex scapular","Profunda brachii"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecircumflex scapular artery\u003C/strong\u003E is found in the triangular space of the shoulder region. This space is bordered by the teres minor, teres major, and the long head of the triceps brachii. The circumflex scapular artery passes through this space to supply blood to the scapular region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPosterior circumflex humeral artery\u003C/strong\u003E - This artery is found in the quadrangular space, not the triangular space\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuprascapular artery\u003C/strong\u003E - This artery travels over the superior border of the scapula, not through the triangular space\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDorsal scapular artery\u003C/strong\u003E - This artery supplies the medial border of the scapula, not through the triangular space\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProfunda brachii artery\u003C/strong\u003E - This artery is located in the arm, not in the shoulder region\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The circumflex scapular artery is located in the triangular space of the shoulder region.","The triangular space is bordered by the teres minor, teres major, and the long head of the triceps brachii.","The triangular space allows passage of the circumflex scapular artery from the axillary region to the scapular region."],"references":["West, S. G. (2019). Anatomy and physiology of the musculoskeletal system. Rheumatology Secrets E-Book: Rheumatology Secrets E-Book, 17","Miniato MA, Anand P, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder. 2023 Jul 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725618","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","McCausland C, Sawyer E, Eovaldi BJ, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Shoulder and Upper Limb, Shoulder Muscles. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure I